# API Integration Rules

## CLOB V2 Migration
- CLOB V2 go-live: April 28, 2026 ~11:00 UTC.
- V2 uses pUSD collateral, new exchange contracts, and new signing fields.
- V2 removes nonce, feeRateBps, taker from user-set order fields.
- V2 adds timestamp, metadata, builder to order fields.
- Open orders are wiped at cutover.
- Before cutover: test against https://clob-v2.polymarket.com
- After cutover: production at https://clob.polymarket.com

## Verification-First
- If API behavior is uncertain, verify against official docs or live read-only endpoints BEFORE coding.
- If docs and live behavior disagree, live behavior wins only after reproduced and documented.
- Mark implementation areas BLOCKED if verification fails or is ambiguous.
- Capture evidence: command, timestamp, endpoint, sanitized response, result (PASS/FAIL/BLOCKED).
- See API_VERIFICATION.md for full checklist.

## Endpoints
- Market discovery: GET https://gamma-api.polymarket.com/markets/keyset
- CLOB market info: GET https://clob.polymarket.com/clob-markets/{condition_id}
- WebSocket: wss://ws-subscriptions-clob.polymarket.com/ws/market
- Geoblock: GET https://polymarket.com/api/geoblock
- Fee rate: GET https://clob.polymarket.com/fee-rate?token_id={token_id}
- Server time: GET https://clob.polymarket.com/time

## Fee Model
- Makers: zero fees.
- Takers: pay fees on fee-enabled markets.
- Fee rate determined at match time, not set by user in V2.
- All taker paper fills MUST include taker fees.

## Geoblock
- Check at startup BEFORE any trading-capable mode.
- Blocked = true → fail closed. No bypass.
- Persist geoblock result with the run.

## Rate Limits
- REST only for startup, recovery, metadata.
- WebSocket for all live market data.
- Include conservative polling intervals and request budgets in config.
- Rate-limit responses → degraded state, not silent failure.
